15:52.410 --> 15:54.511
(whispers) It's that way.

16:01.586 --> 16:05.889
You gotta be kidding me.

16:05.890 --> 16:07.892
(Ryan) You think he's in there?

16:07.893 --> 16:09.393
(Esposito) It is daytime.

16:09.394 --> 16:12.263
If he thinks he's a vampire,
that's where he'd be.

16:15.834 --> 16:17.501
I'll cover you.

16:17.502 --> 16:19.237
Together?

16:19.238 --> 16:21.405
All right. On three.

16:21.406 --> 16:22.773
Okay.

16:22.774 --> 16:25.576
One...
One...

16:25.577 --> 16:27.345
Two...
Two...

16:27.346 --> 16:29.914
Three.
Three.

16:29.915 --> 16:31.983
It's empty.
(laughs)

16:31.984 --> 16:34.986
(Ryan) you see him jump?
(laughs) Real macho, Castle.

16:34.987 --> 16:36.354
(laughs)

16:36.355 --> 16:38.890
Hey!
Hey hey, hey, hey!

16:38.891 --> 16:41.158
Get him off!
Get him off!

16:41.159 --> 16:42.860
Get him off me!

16:42.861 --> 16:44.362
Get him off of him.

16:44.363 --> 16:46.163
Aah! He bit me.

16:46.164 --> 16:48.266
Look!
He is a vampire.

16:48.267 --> 16:52.069
(groaning)

16:54.084 --> 16:57.320
(muttering)

16:57.321 --> 16:59.522
He's not a vampire.

16:59.523 --> 17:01.491
But his skin burned
when the light hit him.

17:01.492 --> 17:04.527
He has porphyria. Some people
call it the vampire disease.

17:04.528 --> 17:08.097
Its symptoms include
extreme photosensitivity.
(muttering continues)

17:08.098 --> 17:10.766
The skin blisters when it's
exposed to the sun.

17:10.767 --> 17:13.801
Victims are prone
to hallucinations, paranoia.

17:13.803 --> 17:15.671
That explains
his psych diagnosis.

17:15.672 --> 17:17.573
Exactly how contagious is it?

17:17.574 --> 17:19.142
It's a genetic disease.

17:19.143 --> 17:21.676
Besides, I put enough
antibiotics on that bite

17:21.678 --> 17:24.113
to kill a small animal.

17:24.114 --> 17:26.582
Now if we're done here,
I gotta head back to the slab

17:26.583 --> 17:29.952
and see a man about a corpse.
Thank you, Dr. Parish.
Castle was totally freaked out.

17:29.953 --> 17:32.555
You want to bite me?
You buy me dinner.

17:32.556 --> 17:36.058
(Morgan muttering)

17:40.364 --> 17:43.799
(muttering continues)

17:45.902 --> 17:48.204
Mr. Lockerby.
(mutters)

17:53.610 --> 17:55.778
(muttering)

17:55.779 --> 17:58.847
Morlock, do you know
somebody named Crow?

17:58.848 --> 18:00.616
Heartless bitch!

18:00.617 --> 18:02.685
Spots all over.

18:02.686 --> 18:05.020
S-spots all over.

18:05.021 --> 18:07.923
Were you in the cemetery with Crow?
Blood all over!

18:07.924 --> 18:09.525
Blood all over.

18:09.526 --> 18:11.327
There's been a murder,
Mr. Lockerby.

18:11.328 --> 18:13.362
Do you understand that?

18:13.363 --> 18:15.798
(mutters)
were you in the cemetery with Crow?

18:15.799 --> 18:18.801
We found a wooden stake with
your fingerprints all over it.

18:18.802 --> 18:21.070
Ah! The cat creeps in
to kill the bird.

18:21.071 --> 18:23.005
I should've buried you then,
wicked boy.

18:23.006 --> 18:25.208
I should've buried you then.

18:25.209 --> 18:27.357
Can--I didn't see.
I didn't see. I didn't see.

18:27.678 --> 18:29.613
I don't want to tell
the public defender

18:29.614 --> 18:31.615
how to do her job,
but I'm gonna say

18:31.616 --> 18:33.617
that the insanity plea
might be appropriate.

18:33.618 --> 18:36.119
Maybe the state psychiatrist
can help us make sense

18:36.120 --> 18:38.922
out of Morlock's rantings
before they take him away.
(telephone rings)

18:38.923 --> 18:41.491
Beckett.

18:41.492 --> 18:43.226
Okay.

18:43.227 --> 18:45.194
Thanks.
That was the lab.

18:45.195 --> 18:47.497
They were calling me
to tell me

18:47.498 --> 18:50.099
that the smudge on the stake
was India ink.

18:50.100 --> 18:52.035
Morlock must have gotten some
on his hands

18:52.036 --> 18:54.804
Going through a dumpster.
India ink?

18:54.805 --> 18:58.074
Yeah. Why?
India ink, or Chinese ink,

18:58.075 --> 19:00.644
Has been used
since 4th century B.C.

19:00.645 --> 19:02.746
When it was called masi.

19:02.747 --> 19:05.815
It's water-resistant, so it
won't smudge when colored over.

19:05.816 --> 19:08.351
It's also the ink used
by letterers in comic books.

19:08.352 --> 19:11.354
So if Crow was the illustrator...
Then Crow's friend Daemon
was the letterer.

19:11.355 --> 19:15.224
But what would the ink
be doing on the stake?
What indeed.

19:15.225 --> 19:17.861
You guys, where are we on the friend?
We're working on it.

19:17.862 --> 19:20.897
Yeah? Well, could you
work a little faster?
Hey, Castle, you wanna help?

19:20.898 --> 19:22.933
I would love to,

19:22.934 --> 19:26.069
but I have got
bigger pumpkins to carve.

19:26.070 --> 19:29.505
