19:32.643 --> 19:34.644
(tool whirring)

19:34.645 --> 19:37.313
How's your Nosferatu coming?

19:37.314 --> 19:39.248
The key to a good jack-o'-lantern

19:39.249 --> 19:41.618
Is understanding negative space.

19:41.619 --> 19:44.454
It's not what's there.
It's what's not there.

19:44.455 --> 19:47.057
Ah, I have taught you well,
grasshopper.

19:47.058 --> 19:49.525
Oh. What are my two
pumpkin masters carving

19:49.526 --> 19:51.360
for this year's party?

19:51.361 --> 19:53.296
I am carving the traditional
jack-o'-lantern--

19:53.297 --> 19:55.665
Mr. Scary pumpkin face.

19:55.666 --> 19:58.068
Aw.

19:58.069 --> 20:00.837
And I am carving Max Schreck
in his role as Count Orlok.

20:00.838 --> 20:04.574
Dad's a little vampire obsessed
because of his case.
Mm-hmm.

20:04.575 --> 20:07.777
Or maybe it's because
of the bite.

20:07.778 --> 20:09.779
I swear,
you have missed your calling.

20:09.780 --> 20:12.148
I don't even know
why you bother to write.

20:12.149 --> 20:15.118
Hey, you want to carve with us?
Oh, can't. I'm off to a masquerade ball.

20:15.119 --> 20:17.520
Perhaps I'll meet my Gatsby.

20:17.521 --> 20:19.923
Oh.
Oh! Mother, I'm impressed.

20:19.924 --> 20:23.026
You still fit into your prom dress.
Oh, thank you, darling.

20:23.027 --> 20:26.696
(lowered voice) have you asked him yet?
(lowered voice) I was waiting
for the right moment.

20:26.697 --> 20:28.498
Oh.
(lowered voice) asked me what?

20:28.499 --> 20:31.400
(normal voice) Paige and I got
invited to a party tomorrow--

20:31.401 --> 20:34.403
the night before Halloween-- by seniors.
By your grandmother's friends?

20:34.404 --> 20:37.674
No, dad. Twelfth graders.
But it'll be supervised.

20:37.675 --> 20:40.644
(sighs) This is one of those
crossroads moments, isn't it?

20:40.645 --> 20:42.145
Oh, let her go.

20:42.146 --> 20:44.714
She's far more responsible
than you ever were.

20:44.715 --> 20:46.449
Yes, you can go.

20:46.450 --> 20:49.019
<i>But if anything happens that
makes you feel uncomfortable,</i>

20:49.020 --> 20:52.856
anything at all, you call me.
I don't care what it is.

20:52.857 --> 20:54.958
And there'll be no punishments,
no recriminations, nothing,

20:54.959 --> 20:57.661
I promise, just so long as you call.
Okay.

20:57.662 --> 21:00.530
Yeah, yeah, I will, I promise.
But nothing's gonna happen.

21:00.531 --> 21:02.699
But there's one more thing, though.
Yes.

21:02.700 --> 21:04.801
Will you watch Feggin?
Why, is he gonna hatch?

21:04.802 --> 21:07.537
No. Our health teacher says
we can't leave him alone.

21:07.538 --> 21:09.806
That's considered egg abuse.

21:09.807 --> 21:11.875
And since Paige and I
are co-parenting,

21:11.876 --> 21:13.910
and we're both
going to the party

21:13.911 --> 21:17.313
and her parents are going out,
we need a sitter.
Oh, no. Sorry. Uh, plans.

21:17.314 --> 21:19.816
Yeah, okay. Sure. I'll watch
your little egg child.

21:19.817 --> 21:23.452
But I want you to know, I'm far
too young to be a grandparent.

21:23.453 --> 21:26.089
And if, uh, any of those
senior boys bother you...

21:26.090 --> 21:28.524
(imitates Norman Bates)
father won't be quite himself.

21:28.525 --> 21:30.493
(tool whirring)

21:30.494 --> 21:34.363
(laughs evilly)

21:36.466 --> 21:38.868
(coughs)
(Beckett) he mumbles,

21:38.869 --> 21:40.870
he shouts, he throws himself
against the bars,

21:40.871 --> 21:42.872
but the's just
something about it.

21:42.873 --> 21:45.041
Although someone
like Mr. Lockerby

21:45.042 --> 21:47.977
will present as completely
non compos mentis...
Mm-hmm.

21:47.978 --> 21:50.747
He could still have moments
of lucidity.

21:50.748 --> 21:52.749
The difficulty

21:52.750 --> 21:55.518
is separating the fantasy
from the reality.

21:55.519 --> 21:57.553
Well, these were drawn
by our victim.

21:57.554 --> 21:59.522
I was wondering
if they suggested anything

21:59.523 --> 22:02.491
about his relationship
with Mr. Lockerby.

22:05.429 --> 22:08.264
I'd have to study them more
to give you a diagnosis,

22:08.265 --> 22:10.433
but these are more about
the woman in the drawings

22:10.434 --> 22:12.468
than Lockerby.
What do you mean?

22:12.469 --> 22:14.570
He draws her as an angel,

22:14.571 --> 22:17.073
but always in the context
of an act of violence.

22:17.074 --> 22:20.309
Honestly? It looks to me like the work
of someone who was once traumatized.

22:20.310 --> 22:23.379
Uh, childhood trauma.
What'd I tell you?

22:23.380 --> 22:25.448
Doc Holloway,
this is Richard Castle.

22:25.449 --> 22:28.084
Dr. Holloway. Say hello to
the nice psychiatrist, Feggin.

22:28.085 --> 22:29.518
Hello.

22:31.488 --> 22:33.689
I will arrange for someone

22:33.690 --> 22:36.525
from social services
to come get Mr. Lockerby.

22:36.526 --> 22:39.729
And if you want, I can have
someone get him, too.
(whispers) Yes, please.

22:39.730 --> 22:41.731
(normal voice) Are you gonna eat that?

22:41.732 --> 22:44.367
Eat my own grandchild?
What am I, a monster?

22:44.368 --> 22:46.402
Maybe that bite
was catching.

22:46.403 --> 22:48.371
It's a school
health sciences project--

22:48.372 --> 22:50.506
Helping de-romanticize
having a family

22:50.507 --> 22:53.076
before you're ready
to take responsibility.
Mm.

22:53.077 --> 22:55.411
Alexis and Paige
are going to

22:55.412 --> 22:58.114
their first senior party
tonight, so I'm babysitting.

22:58.115 --> 22:59.949
Egg-sitting.
Senior party, huh?

22:59.950 --> 23:01.751
What?

23:01.752 --> 23:04.287
(telephone rings)

23:04.288 --> 23:06.389
Beckett.
(mouths word)

23:06.390 --> 23:08.858
We showed Crow's picture
around the neighborhood.

23:08.859 --> 23:10.827
We got a lead
on his friend Daemon.

23:10.828 --> 23:13.496
You're not gonna believe this.
The guy is dead.

23:13.497 --> 23:16.065
Shot right through the heart,
and his place has been tossed.

23:16.066 --> 23:19.669
Oh... And, uh...

23:19.670 --> 23:22.571
He's a werewolf.

23:26.271 --> 23:28.439
Silver bullet?

23:28.440 --> 23:31.841
No, 9 millimeter.
Then I guess he's not a real werewolf.

23:31.842 --> 23:34.911
Nice. The hairs on his face
and hands are synthetic,

23:34.912 --> 23:37.214
attached with spirit gum.

23:37.215 --> 23:40.584
It's a Halloween costume.
According to his driver's license,

23:40.585 --> 23:43.120
Daemon's real name
was Jonas Westfall.

23:43.121 --> 23:45.155
He's a graduate student--
N.Y.U.--

23:45.156 --> 23:46.990
In forensic anthropology.

23:46.991 --> 23:49.359
Then that explains the bones.

23:49.360 --> 23:51.228
Castle, don't touch.
I know.

23:51.229 --> 23:53.397
(Ryan) Canvassed the building.

23:53.398 --> 23:58.302
Neighbor remembers hearing
something the other day,

23:58.303 --> 24:00.370
based on deterioration
and lividity

24:00.371 --> 24:02.372
and the smell of that
old Thai food,

24:02.373 --> 24:05.209
wolf boy was killed
the same day as our vampire.

24:05.210 --> 24:07.344
I'd say a couple of hours before.

24:07.345 --> 24:09.313
Ryan, track down the delivery guy.

24:09.314 --> 24:11.515
Find out when this was delivered

24:11.516 --> 24:14.184
and whether anyone else
was up here when he brought it.

24:14.185 --> 24:16.520
"Come as your alter ego"?

24:16.521 --> 24:19.623
"October 27th at 7:00 P.M."
our guy was going to this party.

24:19.624 --> 24:22.292
Same day that Crow was killed.

24:22.293 --> 24:24.328
(Lanie) I assume there's a connection.
(Castle) Hey.

24:24.329 --> 24:25.862
India ink,

24:25.863 --> 24:28.698
which means Crow's killer
was in the apartment, too.

24:28.699 --> 24:31.168
(Beckett) but what
were they looking for?

24:33.771 --> 24:35.472
Castle.

24:37.208 --> 24:38.908
Morlock?

24:38.909 --> 24:41.845
He comes here, shoots Daemon,
grabs a stake goes off and kills Crow.

24:41.846 --> 24:45.015
And in the struggle,
the ink bottle is broken.

24:45.016 --> 24:49.052
Wasn't Morlock. This victim
was killed during the day.

24:49.053 --> 24:51.955
Morlock had porphyria.
He would've burnt to a crisp.

24:51.956 --> 24:55.492
So if he didn't kill our werewolf...
Then chances are he didn't
kill our vampire.

24:55.493 --> 24:58.862
Well, then how did the prints
get on the stake?
Maybe he was trying to help him.

24:58.863 --> 25:01.165
Maybe he was trying
to save his friend.

25:01.166 --> 25:03.733
Are you sure
about the time of death?

25:03.734 --> 25:06.903
His watch broke when he fell.
It says 4:00, October 27th.

25:06.904 --> 25:09.072
Well, then if it
wasn't Morlock, who was it?

25:09.073 --> 25:11.608
And what were they
looking for?

25:11.609 --> 25:14.077
Uh... I don't know
what they were looking for,

25:14.078 --> 25:16.946
but I think I know
what our vic was hiding.

25:24.556 --> 25:26.990
So Jonas Westfall,
A.K.A. Daemon,

25:26.991 --> 25:29.660
was inches away
from getting his Master's

25:29.661 --> 25:31.895
in forensic science from N.Y.U.

25:31.896 --> 25:33.963
This all looks like
part of his research.

25:33.964 --> 25:35.932
I went through
a bone collecting phase

25:35.933 --> 25:38.368
when I was a kid.

25:38.369 --> 25:40.837
So whatever happened to you
happened when you were young.

25:40.838 --> 25:43.840
What was it, Castle?
Did you witness a murder?

25:43.841 --> 25:46.443
Or did you skin your knee
and it bled?

25:46.444 --> 25:47.911
Hmm. Speaking of trauma,

25:47.912 --> 25:50.814
I wonder how late Alexis
is gonna be at her party.

25:50.815 --> 25:52.849
Poor Feggin is suffering
from separation issues.

25:52.850 --> 25:55.151
Come on, Castle.
You know mine. Tit for tat.

25:55.152 --> 25:57.153
Just because
I've seen your tat

25:57.154 --> 25:59.289
doesn't mean
I'm gonna show you my...

25:59.290 --> 26:02.593
Check this out.
Uh, dated two years ago--

26:02.594 --> 26:05.028
"A murdered woman was unearthed
in the Pennsylvania woods

26:05.029 --> 26:07.030
"above Lehigh River
late Sunday night.

26:07.031 --> 26:08.765
"Investigators say she had been

26:08.766 --> 26:11.735
buried in the shallow grave for years."
And?

26:11.736 --> 26:13.737
"Based on the remains,
investigators have attempted

26:13.738 --> 26:16.072
a forensic reconstruction
of the murdered woman's face."

26:16.073 --> 26:17.941
That's the woman
from Crow's drawings.

26:17.942 --> 26:20.176
Yet in the graphic novel,

26:20.177 --> 26:23.046
she consistently appears
as the angel of death.

26:23.047 --> 26:25.549
Okay, so Crow became obsessed
with Daemon's case study.

26:25.550 --> 26:28.017
Why would they go to
this much trouble to hide it?

26:28.018 --> 26:30.754
Why would someone kill
to find it?

26:30.755 --> 26:33.056
Castle.

26:33.057 --> 26:34.758
Hmm?

26:34.759 --> 26:37.361
These sketches
were drawn four years ago.

26:37.362 --> 26:38.928
No, no that's impossible.

26:38.929 --> 26:41.030
This body wasn't discovered
until two years ago.

26:41.031 --> 26:42.866
So either Crow
is psychic or...

26:42.867 --> 26:45.736
Or he knew this woman
before she died.

26:45.737 --> 26:49.439
(cell phone rings and beeps)
Hey, Alexis. How you doing?
Everything okay?

26:49.440 --> 26:51.007
No, dad. It's Paige.

26:51.008 --> 26:53.744
I think the punch is spiked,
and she had too much to drink.

26:53.745 --> 26:56.880
I'm afraid something's
gonna happen to her.
I'm on my way.

27:01.286 --> 27:03.587
Oh, my god.
Is she all right?

27:03.588 --> 27:06.055
I don't know. She was
swapping drinks for kisses,

27:06.056 --> 27:09.092
and I tried to pull her away,
but she wouldn't let me.

27:09.093 --> 27:12.362
Would you get me a glass of water?
(Paige, slurring words)
leave me alone, 'lexis.

27:12.363 --> 27:14.765
Paige.
Now you're sure she hasn't been
throwing up or unconscious?

27:14.766 --> 27:17.200
No, just falling down.
All right. Call her parents.

27:17.201 --> 27:20.637
(slurring) don't do it.
Oh, my 'rents... 'urder me.

27:20.638 --> 27:23.973
Don' do it, Mr. Castle.
Jus' let me sleep over.

27:23.974 --> 27:25.776
What is she saying?
It's just drunk talk.

27:25.777 --> 27:27.877
She says don't call her parents
or they'll murder her.

27:27.878 --> 27:30.113
Just let her sleep over.
Do we have to call her parents?

27:30.114 --> 27:33.149
We do. Get me their number.
She'll get in so much trouble.

27:33.150 --> 27:35.084
Less than if you
had left her there.

27:35.085 --> 27:37.854
(mouths word)
Now.

27:37.855 --> 27:41.458
(keypad beeps)

27:41.459 --> 27:44.961
Try to get her to drink that.
Please.

27:48.301 --> 27:52.070
Adora.
That's what he called her.

27:52.071 --> 27:54.673
We've seen her in Matthew's
artwork for years.

27:54.674 --> 27:57.075
Do you know who she is?

27:57.076 --> 28:00.012
No, we just assumed that she was
a figment of his imagination.

28:00.013 --> 28:03.382
He called her
his own personal ghost.

28:03.383 --> 28:06.184
He said she appeared
in his dreams and nightmares.

28:06.185 --> 28:09.021
Well, she's not a figment.

28:09.022 --> 28:10.623
She's very real.

28:14.895 --> 28:18.230
Are you sure
you don't recognize her?

28:18.231 --> 28:20.265
Because she could be anybody.

28:20.266 --> 28:22.735
She could be a teacher, a neighbor.
No, I-I'm certain.

28:22.736 --> 28:24.937
We've only seen her
in his art.

28:24.938 --> 28:27.606
Do you know if your son
experienced anything traumatic

28:27.607 --> 28:29.774
when he was younger?
What do you mean?

28:29.775 --> 28:31.810
I showed some of
Matthew's drawings

28:31.811 --> 28:35.280
to one of our therapists,
and he said that it looked like

28:35.281 --> 28:37.182
he might have witnessed
something disturbing,

28:37.183 --> 28:39.151
seen something very violent.

28:39.152 --> 28:42.521
I-I really can't think of anything.

28:42.522 --> 28:45.624
Do you have any of
Matthew's earlier drawings

28:45.625 --> 28:47.092
of this woman?

28:47.093 --> 28:49.928
No. He took it all
with him when he left.
Yeah.

28:49.929 --> 28:51.931
Um, you might want to check
the portfolio

28:51.932 --> 28:54.466
with his application for Barker.

28:54.467 --> 28:58.236
All the work he cared about,
he put in there.
Thank you, Rosie. We'll look into it.

29:03.577 --> 29:05.143
What, no Castle?

29:05.144 --> 29:08.948
Uh, no. He had a late night.
What's up?

29:08.949 --> 29:10.916
I was talking to
the Pennsylvania state police

29:10.917 --> 29:12.817
about our victim's mystery woman,
and they said I was the second person

29:12.818 --> 29:15.888
to call in the last two weeks about
the woman they found in the woods.

29:15.889 --> 29:18.724
Did they tell you who else called?

29:18.725 --> 29:20.358
Jonas Westfall.

29:20.359 --> 29:22.294
Daemon.
Yep, our werewolf.

29:22.295 --> 29:24.663
And their forensics expert
determined that

29:24.664 --> 29:27.666
the woman died 18 years ago from
a gunshot wound to the chest

29:27.667 --> 29:30.869
from a 9-millimeter handgun.
Same as Daemon.

29:30.870 --> 29:33.872
So I thought, what the hell?
Compare the ballistics.

29:33.873 --> 29:35.908
The bullets... are a match.

29:35.909 --> 29:38.811
Two murders
that many years apart?

29:38.812 --> 29:40.846
Anything on the mystery woman?

29:40.847 --> 29:43.716
Mnh-mnh.
Still haven't I.D.'ed her.

29:43.717 --> 29:45.517
You know, Crow would've been
2 years old

29:45.518 --> 29:47.086
when that woman was killed.

29:47.087 --> 29:49.989
Do you remember anything
from when you were that young?

29:49.990 --> 29:51.690
Beckett.

29:51.691 --> 29:53.158
Crow's portfolio?

29:53.159 --> 29:54.693
Yeah.

29:54.694 --> 29:57.896
And there's something
you gotta see.

29:57.897 --> 30:00.666
(Ryan) look familiar?

30:05.404 --> 30:07.405
(Beckett) it's the same tree,

30:07.406 --> 30:09.441
just like where the body was found.

30:09.442 --> 30:11.610
You don't draw something with
that precision from a dream.

30:11.611 --> 30:13.879
He's remembering it.

30:13.880 --> 30:16.782
Crow witnessed that woman's
murder when he was 2 years old.

30:16.783 --> 30:19.118
He had to have been
with someone--a sitter

30:19.119 --> 30:21.586
or a family member
or maybe even the killer.

30:21.587 --> 30:23.588
Run a background check
on the Freemans.

30:23.589 --> 30:25.791
Find out where they were living
18 years ago.
You got it.

30:27.861 --> 30:31.063
Hey, Castle.
Alexis okay?

30:31.064 --> 30:34.199
She's, uh...
She's a smart kid.

30:34.200 --> 30:36.301
You took care of Feggin.

30:36.302 --> 30:39.437
Yeah, well, he was... easy.

30:39.438 --> 30:42.340
He didn't even fuss
when I put him to bed.

30:42.341 --> 30:46.378
Yo. Ready for more tales
of the weird and strangely odd?

30:46.379 --> 30:48.446
We looked into
the Freeman family history.

30:48.447 --> 30:50.549
Freeman is Janice's maiden name.

30:50.550 --> 30:52.851
When she and Alan got married,
Alan took her name

30:52.852 --> 30:54.753
and so did Matthew.

30:54.754 --> 30:57.355
Well, he's either a feminist
or he's hiding something.

30:57.356 --> 31:01.226
What's Alan's original last name?
McGinty. And I think
he was hiding something.

31:01.227 --> 31:03.328
Alan's first wife, Elizabeth McGinty,

31:03.329 --> 31:05.164
went missing from
Summit, New Jersey,

31:05.165 --> 31:06.899
18 years ago.

31:06.900 --> 31:08.667
She was never found.

31:08.668 --> 31:10.769
Alan lied to us.

31:10.770 --> 31:12.805
He knew exactly
who his son was drawing.

31:12.806 --> 31:15.774
He was drawing
his real mother.

31:15.775 --> 31:18.543
And Summit's only a couple of hours
from where the body was found.

31:18.544 --> 31:20.879
Elizabeth McGinty, maiden name Dryden.

31:20.880 --> 31:22.981
Dryden?

31:22.982 --> 31:24.649
Elizabeth Dryden.

31:24.650 --> 31:27.119
What?
Question mark.

31:27.120 --> 31:29.654
Remember what I told you about
gravestones telling stories?

31:29.655 --> 31:32.457
(Beckett) Crow came here
for a reason.

31:32.458 --> 31:35.194
So cemetery management
said that the family

31:35.195 --> 31:37.162
had a memorial service
for their daughter

31:37.163 --> 31:39.598
about five years after she went missing.
Daemon must have looked

31:39.599 --> 31:42.567
at hundreds of reconstructed
faces researching his thesis.

31:42.568 --> 31:45.503
I can't imagine the shock
when he recognized one

31:45.504 --> 31:48.006
as the woman from Crow's drawings.
And Crow must have realized

31:48.007 --> 31:50.675
his family had been
lying to him all these years.

31:50.676 --> 31:53.178
(Beckett) Huh.
Fresh flowers on her grave.

31:53.179 --> 31:55.147
Crow brought
his father here

31:55.148 --> 31:57.382
to confront him
with his mother's grave.

32:01.329 --> 32:02.595
All of these years,

32:02.596 --> 32:04.630
You knew your son
was drawing his mother,

32:04.631 --> 32:07.267
and you never said anything.
I was protecting my family.

32:07.268 --> 32:10.103
You were protecting yourself.
You're a cold-blooded killer.

32:10.104 --> 32:12.705
You killed your wife, and then
reported her missing,

32:12.706 --> 32:15.141
and then 18 years later
when your son found out,

32:15.142 --> 32:18.378
you killed him as well.
You don't have to respond to that.

32:18.379 --> 32:21.581
No, no, no, no. She's accusing
me of killing my son.

32:21.582 --> 32:24.717
Yes, I lied to Matthew,
but I did it to protect him.

32:24.718 --> 32:27.354
I thought he was too young to understand.
You were a suspect.

32:27.355 --> 32:29.589
Of course I was a suspect.
I was her husband.

32:29.590 --> 32:32.658
There wasn't any evidence that
tied me to her disappearance

32:32.659 --> 32:35.362
'cause I had
nothing to do with it.

32:35.363 --> 32:39.165
When Janice and I got married,
it was like a chance...

32:39.166 --> 32:41.368
A chance at a fresh start.

32:41.369 --> 32:43.669
And so as soon
as you were legally able,

32:43.670 --> 32:46.572
you married your nanny.

32:46.573 --> 32:48.674
Janice was there for us

32:48.675 --> 32:51.477
during a very dark time
in our lives.

32:51.478 --> 32:53.346
We had press on the lawn.

32:53.347 --> 32:55.382
There were days without sleep.

32:55.383 --> 32:58.385
I was handing out flyers
with Lizzy's picture on it.

32:58.386 --> 33:01.621
And Janice kept it together,
and she protected Matthew.

33:01.622 --> 33:05.191
Then why would you lie to us?
You told us in front of our daughter.

33:05.192 --> 33:06.826
What did you want me to do,

33:06.827 --> 33:09.195
tell her that everything
she thought was a lie?

33:09.196 --> 33:12.498
Rosie adored Matthew.
She had just found out he died.

33:12.499 --> 33:15.001
What would you have done?

33:15.002 --> 33:17.037
I would've told her
the truth.

33:19.706 --> 33:23.009
He was 9 years old
when he first drew her face.

33:24.946 --> 33:28.014
He showed it to me.
I thought I was seeing a ghost.

33:28.015 --> 33:31.184
I figured... She was still
somewhere in his head

33:31.185 --> 33:34.454
from his early memories.

33:34.455 --> 33:37.390
But we'd been living a lie
for so long,

33:37.391 --> 33:39.659
it had become the truth.

33:39.660 --> 33:42.862
So how could I possibly tell him
that Janice wasn't his mother,

33:42.863 --> 33:45.698
that his real mother ran away?

33:45.699 --> 33:48.668
Are we through here, Detective?
Not by a long shot, Lawson.

33:48.669 --> 33:50.636
The Connecticut state police

33:50.637 --> 33:52.705
found a 9-millimeter handgun
in your client's home,

33:52.706 --> 33:55.675
and I am just betting that
that is the same gun that killed

33:55.676 --> 33:57.677
Elizabeth Dryden McGinty
and Jonas Westfall.

33:57.678 --> 34:00.780
No, I-- don't say anything, Alan.

34:00.781 --> 34:03.416
Oh, yeah.
And there's also this.

34:03.417 --> 34:07.454
Your son witnessed
his mother's murder.

34:15.795 --> 34:17.663
No.

34:17.664 --> 34:21.967
That's not possible.

34:23.437 --> 34:27.706
How... How is this possible?

34:27.708 --> 34:29.208
Here. Thank you.

34:29.210 --> 34:31.444
Ahem. Excuse me.

34:31.445 --> 34:34.414
Um, how much longer are
you people gonna keep us waiting

34:34.415 --> 34:36.549
without letting us know
what is going on?

34:36.550 --> 34:39.784
We are trying to find
the answers, Mrs. Freeman.

34:39.786 --> 34:42.255
(scoffs)

34:47.628 --> 34:49.996
Spots.
What?

34:49.996 --> 34:51.998
"Spots all over.
Blood all over.

34:51.998 --> 34:54.667
